genresAdvancedInfo.name: rock caipira
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Rock caipira is a subgenre of rock music that originated in Brazil. It is heavily influenced by traditional Brazilian country music, known as sertanejo, and features lyrics that often reflect rural life. The instrumentation typically includes acoustic guitars, violins, and accordions, and the tempo is generally slower than traditional rock music.
